He owns Leftorium Express, a downsized version of his former business The Leftorium and a home business, Flancrest Enterprises, which makes religious hook rugs. He struggles to control the crumbling school and is constantly engaged in a battle against its inadequate resources, apathetic and bitter teachers, and often rowdy and unenthusiastic students, Bart Simpson being a standout example. A strict disciplinarian, Skinner has an uptight, militaristic attitude that stems from his years in the United States Army as a Green Beret, which included service in the Vietnam War, where he achieved the rank of a sergeant, according to his rank insignia. As a result of his service in the Vietnam War, he is often plagued by horrible memories of his involvement via post-traumatic stress disorder, sometimes even happening at the most inopportune of times. He hosts the Channel 6 weekday news (Scott Christian is the weekend news anchor and Kent's fill-in) as well as Smartline, a local current affairs show, and also Eye on Springfield, which focuses mostly on Springfield's entertainment news. He also is a failed musician who toys with the idea of being a math teacher.

name: Groundskeeper Willie
occupation: Groundskeeper and Janitor at Springfield Elementary School
phrases: THEN GREASE ME UP, WOMAN!!!
Save yer strength, lad! Theres a whole field for you to resod yet!
Ach! Sounds like that gopher I caught in me lawnmower!
Guess theres some stones in your leaf bag, after all.
Save me from the wee turtles! They were too quick for me!
Uh-oh. The little fat boy and his family are in trouble.
Willie hears ya, Willie dont care.
Brothers and sisters are natural enemies, like Englishmen and Scots! Or Welshmen and Scots! Or Japanese and Scots! Or Scots and  Scots! Damn Scots! They ruined Scotland!
description: Dr. William "Willie" MacDougal III (Scots Gaelic: Uilleam MacDhùghaill), also known as William Sean McLavel, G.K. Willington Esquire, and William MacMoran, best known as Groundskeeper Willie (Scots Gaelic: Fear-gleidhidh talmhainn Uilleam) is the groundskeeper and janitor of Springfield Elementary School and a minor character in The Simpsons Movie who's originally from Scotland. Willie's job is to supervise the children of the school during recess, and clean the halls. He is recognizable for his red hair and thick Scottish accent. He is often either a formidable enemy or an invaluable ally to Bart and Lisa Simpson; mostly, he has a strained relationship with Principal Seymour Skinner. Willie's either originally from the Scottish town of Kirkwall or a place called North Kilttown, which is likely a reference to the hamlet of Domaduir, near Kyle of Lochalsh. Willie is 45 years old.

name: Cletus Spuckler
description: Cletus Delroy Montfort DeMontblanc Bigglesworth Spuckler, also known as Cletus the Slack-Jawed Yokel, is a stereotypical redneck with a good-natured personality. He is thin and is usually portrayed wearing a pair of jeans and an undershirt. He resides with his family on Rural Route 9 in Springfield. He is sister/wife to Brandine Spuckler, and it is heavily implied throughout the series that they are in some way related (possibly brother and sister), and having their children together makes the two consanguinamorous.

name: Brandine Spuckler
phrases: Dang Cletus!
description: Brandine Spuckler is the sister/wife of Cletus Spuckler. She is a stereotypical hillbilly and the mother of her brother/husband's countless Spuckler Children on an old, run-down farm on Rural Route 9.

name: Dr. Nick
phrases: Hi, everybody!
description: Dr. Nicholas "Nick" Riviera M.D., better known as Dr. Nick, is a recurring character on The Simpsons and a cameo character in The Simpsons Movie.

name: Elizabeth Hoover
description: Elizabeth Gunderson, B.Ed. (née Hoover; also known as Miss Hoover) is a recurring character on The Simpsons. She is a second-grade teacher at Springfield Elementary School.

name: Mona Simpson
phrases: You awful, awful man, get out of my sons grave!
It wasnt your fault, sweetie.
description: Mona Penelope Simpson (née Olsen), also known as Sunny, and formerly Penelope Olsen, was the mother of Homer Simpson, mother-in-law of Marge Simpson, paternal grandmother of Bart, Lisa and Maggie Simpson and first wife of Abraham Simpson II.

name: Troy McClure
phrases: Hi! Im Troy McClure! You may remember me from such [films, TV shows, dates] as...
description: Trodden "Troy" McClure is a cheesy B-movie actor who had fallen on hard times. He was often seen shilling for shoddy products or hosting questionable shows. He appeared from Season 2 until Season 10. Since then, Troy along with two other Phil Hartman characters were retired due to his death.

name: Timothy Lovejoy Jr.
occupation: Reverend of the First Church of Springfield
phrases: Hello, Ned.Damn Flanders.
description: Timothy Goren Lovejoy Jr., better known as Reverand Lovejoy, is a recurring character on The Simpsons. He is the local Presbylutheran Minister in Springfield.

name: Helen Lovejoy
phrases: Wont somebody please think of the children?
Ned Flanders is on the phone.
description: Helen Lovejoy (née Schwartzbaum) is Reverend Timothy Lovejoy's judgmental and gossipy wife and the mother of Jessica Lovejoy. It is hinted that she is the godmother of Lisa and Bart Simpson. Though she can be rude at times, she is very kind to the people she loves and is almost always seen when we see the people of Springfield doing charity or community service. Helen can behave mean and gossipy and is part of a bowling team called The Holly Rollers with members Ned Flanders and Timothy Lovejoy Jr. and ex-member Maude Flanders (deceased) and (most likely) the leader of the Fleet-a-Pita club called the Investorettes with members Agnes Skinner, Luann Van Houten and ex-members Edna Krabappel (deceased), Maude Flanders (deceased) and Marge Simpson, whom the club kicked out in "The Twisted World Of Marge Simpson". Helen was often partnered with Maude Flanders as they protested against the "evils" in Springfield. Her first line was in "Life on The Fast Lane" and it was "Marge? Marge Simpson. You remember me, don't you? I'm Helen Lovejoy the gossipy wife of the Minister." Her catchphrase, “Won't somebody please think of the children?" is used quite often but sometimes, they replace the word "children" with a different word like in "Thanksgiving of Horror", she says "The Pilgrims! Won't somebody please think of the Pilgrims?". Also, in "Pulpit Friction", she says "Why won't somebody blame the children?”. Whenever Ned calls Reverend Lovejoy she says her second catchphrase, “Ned Flanders is on the phone."

name: Jessica Lovejoy
phrases: Youre bad, and I like it.
description: Jessica Lovejoy is the rebellious daughter of Reverend Lovejoy and Helen Lovejoy. She is Bart Simpson's biggest crush after Laura Powers and first girlfriend as well. She was featured as both Bart Simpson's love interest and the main antagonist of "Bart's Girlfriend".

name: Snake Jailbird
phrases: ...Bye!
See ya, cops!
Hoa!
Dude!
description: Snake Jailbird is a recidivist criminal, always getting arrested, but rarely being kept locked up for long. His real name has been referred to as either Chester Turley or Albert Knickerbocker Aloysius Snake, and seemingly before his criminal career, he was known as Detention Bird and Professor Jailbird. He speaks with a "Valley Boy" accent and has a tattoo of a snake on his arm. He is partial to fast cars and fast women and has a knack for reckless abandon. Jailbird is known to associate with criminals including the Springfield Crime Family.

name: Eddie
description: Edward "Eddie" Finnerfield is one of the two police officers who aid Chief Wiggum on almost every mission. Unlike Lou, he is rather unintelligent, but is still smarter than Wiggum is.

name: Kodos
description: Kodos Johnson (pronounced Koh-dohs) is a major antagonist (alongside Kang) of the series. She is a Rigellian from Rigel 7. She is the younger sister of Kang. Together, Kang and Kodos try to take over Earth and are usually seen attacking Springfield.

name: Duffman
phrases: Oh, yeah!
Duffman!
Duffman is here to refill your beer!
description: Duffman, currently known as Puffman, was the mascot and spokesman for the Duff Beer company. His real name is either Barry Duffman or Barry Huffman. The idea of Duffman came about after H.K. Duff's grandfather repurposed a fascist icon because he could not get the rights to Woody Woodpecker. There are actually multiple people who play Duffman. (Others being Sid, Joe, and Larry)

name: Sherri and Terri
phrases: Im Sherri. Shes Terri. (Double balloon)
You must be nice to them - they could surround you!
description: Sherri and Terri Mackleberry are a pair of identical twin students of Springfield Elementary School. Terri is younger than Sherri by two seconds. They are in the same class as Bart, by Edna Krabbapel. They are a little bit strange and sometimes they speak in their own language. They will also not hesitate to berate Bart as seen in various episodes. No one knows whether one twin is Terri or Sherri. However, it has been hinted that they may actually be triplets and the third one is out for revenge, but this has yet to be confirmed on the show, and should be considered non-canon at present. Sherri and Terri have long, purple hair and always wear the same clothes.

name: Jasper Beardsley
phrases: Thats a paddlin.
You sunk my battleship!
description: Jasper Theodore Beardsley is a resident of the Springfield Retirement Castle and is often seen around Springfield. He is Abe Simpson's friend.

name: Jacqueline Bouvier
phrases: I have laryngitis and it hurts to talk. So Ill say one thing. You never do anything right.
You ruined my nap, just like you ruined my daughter’s life.
description: Jacqueline Ingrid "Jackie" Bouvier (née Gurney), occasionally referred to as Mrs. Bouvier or Grandma Bouvier, is the mother of Selma, Patty, Marge, Arthur Bouvier and possibly Hortense, the daughter-in-law of Pepe and Bambi Bouvier, the sister-in-law of Chester, Jojo, Herman and Charlene Bouvier, the maternal grandmother of Bart, Hugo (non-canon), Lisa, Maggie Simpson and Ling Bouvier and the mother-in-law of Homer Simpson, and the widow of the late Clancy Bouvier. She also had a sister named Gladys who died of a bowel obstruction. A family tree showing Jacqueline's known family members can be seen here.

name: Gil Gunderson
description: Gilbert "Gil" Gunderson (usually referred to as Ol' Gil) is an unsuccessful and unlucky businessman of Springfield.

name: Herman Hermann

God closes a door, he opens a gunshop!
Looks like the spider caught himself a couple of flies!
description: Herman Hermann is the owner of Herman's Military Antiques. He dresses in military fatigues.

description: Arthur ''Artie'' Ziff is a minor character in the TV show The Simpsons. A former billionaire and Marge Simpson's senior year prom date from high school, he has attempted to get Marge Simpson to dump Homer Simpson for him and often attempts to kiss her.

name: Lionel Hutz
phrases: HEY, YOU! GET OUT OF MY OFFICE!
Mr. Simpson, this is the most blatant case of fraudulent advertising since my suit against the movie, The Neverending Story!
Youre one of a kind, Marge, and nobody deserves this more than you.
description: Lionel Hutz, also known as Miguel Sanchez, and also known as Dr. Nguyen Van Phuoc, is a lawyer in Springfield, albeit an incompetent one, and removed from the state bar association. He was always desperate for cases, few of which he won. Hutz was financially insolvent, extremely poor and willing to do nearly anything for money. The character of Lionel Hutz, along with other Phil Hartman characters, was retired after the actor's death.

name: Mindy Simmons
phrases: I wanna sneak in a quick nap before lunch.Cant talk. Eating.Homer you know how I feel, so its up to you. Look in your heart. I think youll see what you want.
description: Mindy Simmons was an employee of the Springfield Nuclear Power Plant. She likes the same things as Homer, such as donuts. When Homer met her at work, he found himself highly attracted to her because she was practically a female version of himself.

name: Lindsey Naegle
description: Lindsey Naegle (aka Red) is a resident of Springfield and is often known as Springfield's residential business link.

name: Mrs. Muntz
occupation: Classy Girls Strip Club Pole Dancer
phrases: My mom got too fat to work at Hooters!
description: Mrs. Muntz is Nelson Muntz's mother. She has the same iconic laugh as her son. Nelson often mentioned his parents, and it was often implied that Mrs. Muntz doesn't care for him. She works at the Classy Girls Strip Club, where she is simply known as “Nelson’s mom”.

name: Janey Powell
phrases: Lisa said a dirty word!
Are you going to marry a carrot, Lisa?
Wed like to include you, but you just dont fit in.
With friends like her, who needs acquaintances?
If you pile up all my dolls, itll reach the moon!
description: Janey Powell (variously called Janey Henderson in 2006, Janey Jackson in 2013, Jacqueline Jones in 2016) is Lisa Simpson's best friend, or at least the classmate closest to her, and is Lisa's second most frequently appearing classmate after Ralph Wiggum.

name: Kyle Williams
phrases: Mmya!
description: Kyle Williams, better known as Database, is a student of Springfield Elementary and a member of The Superfriends.

description: Hans Moleman (also known as Ralph Melish, born August 2) is a mole-like man with extremely bad luck.

name: Marvin Monroe
description: Dr. Marvin Monroe was a local counselor who was for a long time considered to have passed on, until he returned, revealing to have "been very sick."

name: Pedro Chespirito
phrases: Ay, ay, ay!
description: Pedro Chespirito, or Bumblebee Man, is the star of a Spanish-language television sitcom on Channel 8, in which he dresses in a bumblebee costume and performs slapstick comedy.

name: Rainier Wolfcastle
description: Rainier Luftwaffe Wolfcastle is an Austrian, musclebound action movie star. Wolfcastle is a veteran of many action movies, most notably the McBain series. Wolfcastle began his acting career as early as childhood in Austria, appearing on long TV commercials advertising bratwurst. He owns a Ferrari F40 and a Hummer H1. He was married to Maria Quimby and has one daughter, Greta Wolfcastle, as well as a son, Dieter Wolfcastle.

name: Frank Grimes
phrases: Im not your buddy, Simpson. I dont like you. In fact, I HATE you! Stay the hell away from me, because from now on, were enemies.

Im saying  whats wrong with America, Simpson. You coast through life, you do as little as possible, and you leech off of decent, hardworking people like me. Heh, if you lived in any other country in the world, youd have starved to death long ago. Youre a fraud, a total fraud.
I cant stand it any longer. This whole plant is insane. Insane, I tell you! (stammers, screams)
Whats this? Extremely high voltage. Well, I dont need safety gloves, because Im Homer Simp-!

We wanted to do an episode where the thinking was What if a real life, normal person had to enter Homers universe and deal with him? I know this episode is controversial and divisive, but I just love it. It really feels like what would happen if a real, somewhat humorless human had to deal with Homer. There was some talk [on NoHomers.net] about the ending—we just did that because 1. it’s really funny and shocking, 2. we like the lesson of sometimes, you just cant win—the whole Frank Grimes episode is a study in frustration and hence Homer has the last laugh and 3. we wanted to show that in real life, being Homer Simpson could be really dangerous and life threatening, as Frank Grimes sadly learned.
description: Franklin "Frank" A. Grimes, Sr. (born 1962; died May 4, 1997) was an employee of the Springfield Nuclear Power Plant and the self-declared enemy of Homer Simpson. Grimes served as the main antagonist of the episode Homer's Enemy. Frank Grimes was a hard worker, who had to earn everything in life the hard way. He was also irritable, grumpy, and easily annoyed, particularly by the actions of his co-worker, Homer.

name: Blue-Haired Lawyer
description: The Blue-Haired Lawyer is Springfield's most prominent lawyer known for his pasty face, blue hair, New York accent, and nasal voice.

name: Richard Texan
description: Richard "Rich" Texan, also known as "The Rich Texan" and Senator Shady Bird Johnson, is a stereotypical rich, callous, but gregarious, business owner from Springfield. He wears a tan suit with a bolo tie and a white cowboy hat (which he wore on the day Kennedy was shot) and is in his 70s. He holds two guns at once.

name: Charlie (SNPP)
occupation: Dangerous Emissions Supervisor at the Springfield Nuclear Power Plant.
phrases: Im Charlie! Everyones favorite Dangerous Emissions Supervisor of Sector 7G!
description: Charlie is the Dangerous Emissions Supervisor of Sector 7G at the Springfield Nuclear Power Plant. He is one of Homer's friends. He drives a Duesenberg J.

name: Manjula Nahasapeemapetilon
description: Manjula Nahasapeemapetilon is the wife of Apu Nahasapeemapetilon and the mother of the Nahasapeemapetilon Octuplets.

name: Wendell Borton
occupation: Fourth grade student at Springfield Elementary School
description: Wendell Borton (also known as Wendell Queasly) is a student at Springfield Elementary School.

name: Laura Powers
phrases: You know, if you were only old enough to grow a bad teenaged moustache, Id go out with you in a second.
description: Laura Powers is a tomboyish teenage girl that moved next door to the Simpsons and the only child of single-parent divorcée Ruth Powers who is understood to be the first crush of Bart Simpson.

name: Grandpa Van Houten
phrases: Me and the new wife travel the country searching for adventure.
description: Jeremy "Grandpa" Van Houten is Kirk and Zack's father and Milhouse's paternal grandfather. He was originally married to Grandma Van Houten, but they got divorced. He remarried and now travels the country in an RV looking for adventure. They won a chili cook-off in Beaumont, Texas.

name: Eleanor Abernathy
occupation: Taking care of cats, Doctor (formerly), Lawyer (formerly)
phrases: Arrrriairar!!
description: Eleanor Abernathy, better known as the Crazy Cat Lady, is a mentally ill hoarder woman who always surrounds herself with a large number of cats. She usually screams gibberish and/or throws her cats at passersby. She gives Lisa one of her cats, Snowball V, who looks exactly like her original Snowball II. She is 40 years old, although she appears elderly.

name: Lurleen Lumpkin
phrases: I used to play the field, I used to be a roamerBut the seasons turning round for me now,I finally bagged me a Homer!
description: Lurleen Lumpkin is an attractive, aspiring country singer from Spittle County. Homer used to be her manager at one point.

name: Rex Banner
occupation: Replacement Chief of PoliceUnited States Treasury Agent
phrases: Are you the Beer Baron?
description: Rex Hugh Banner is the main antagonist in the episode "Homer vs. the Eighteenth Amendment". He is a U.S. Treasury officer in Washington, D.C. who was briefly sent to Springfield to uphold Prohibition in Springfield after Bart got drunk in a live news report, which incited several women to force the city government to declare Prohibition.

name: Wally Kogen
description: Wally Kogen is a travel agent who takes Homer and his friends to the Super Bowl. He and Homer first met in a pyramid scheme and later met while Homer was waiting to get his car tires replaced.

name: L.T. Smash
occupation: LieutenantManager of the Party PosseNavy recruiter

name: Vittorio DiMaggio
phrases: My Apologies!
description: Don Vittorio DiMaggio is a commanding mafia leader, and an old Italian stereotype. The mobsters of the Springfield mafia show him tremendous respect.

name: Kang
description: Kang Johnson is a major antagonist (alongside Kodos) of the series. He is a Rigellian from Rigel 7. He and his younger sister Kodos are continuously trying to take over Earth and are usually seen attacking Springfield. He usually appears in Treehouse of Horrors but either he or Kodos have been seen in other episodes such as "The Springfield Files" and "Gump Roast". Kang and Kodos have a lot of space weaponry on hand and have their own spaceship. They speak the Rigellian language, which, by coincidence, is identical to English. Although they look identical, Kang has a deeper voice than Kodos. He is the featured character on the on the Season 14 DVD/Blu-ray box set as well as the iTunes cover.  According to Kang on the Jerry Springer show, his hearing was advanced enough that not even being confined to a soundproof room was enough to mute out Homer and Springer's conversation before being formally introduced on stage.

name: Richard
phrases: This gets uglier every year, any sign of Bart and Milhouse?
Were never gonna get anything past Principal Skinner.
description: Richard is a student at Springfield Elementary School and one of Bart's friends. He is the best friend of Lewis.

name: Harlan Dondelinger
description: Principal Harlan Dondelinger is the principal of Springfield High School, dating as far back as 1974.

name: Chester J. Lampwick
phrases: Eight-hundred billion dollars.
description: Chester J. Lampwick is the original creator of Itchy, and father of cartoon violence.

phrases: Isnt it amazing the same day you got a pool is the same day we realized we liked you?

description: Terri Mackleberry is the younger twin-sister of Sherri Mackleberry. She is in the same class with Bart Simpson at the Springfield Elementary School.

description: Sherri Mackleberry is the sister of Terri Mackleberry and is the eldest of the twins by two seconds. She is in the same class as Bart Simpson at Springfield Elementary School.

phrases: Kudos, kudos

name: Beatrice Simmons
description: Beatrice “Bea” Simmons was Grandpa Simpson's short-lived girlfriend. She bears a striking resemblance to Mary Bailey.

occupation: 2nd Grade Student at Springfield Elementary School

Hes Wendell, Im Lewis.
description: Lewis Clark is a student in Springfield Elementary School. He is one of Bart's friends, and one of only a handful of African-American students at the school. His best friend is Richard.

name: Sophie Krustofsky
description: Sophie Krustofsky  is an illegitimate daughter of Krusty the Clown and Erin, a female soldier who Krusty had a one-night stand with during the Gulf War.

name: Nikki McKenna
phrases: Hey, vampires are cool outsiders who love girls who hate cheerleaders!
description: Nicole Nell "Nikki" McKenna is a student of Springfield Elementary School.

name: Sam (barfly)
phrases: Okay, okay.
description: Sam is one of the two barflies who's usually seen at Moe's Tavern, along with his late barfly friend, Larry. Their first appearance is in "Simpsons Roasting on an Open Fire". Virtually nothing is known about Sam. He always wears a light green cap and glasses and appears to have severe scoliosis. Sam is a wife dodger, but Homer says good things about him. Sam is 42, just like Larry. Sometimes his cap may have some writing on it, as in "The 7 Beer Itch", it was dusted off to reveal a fire chief cap.

name: Martha Quimby
phrases: Joseph!
description: Martha Quimby is the long-suffering wife of Mayor Quimby and the First Lady of Springfield.

name: Johnny Tightlips
phrases: I aint sayin nothin!
Tell him to suck a lemon.
YOU are a hybrid; Half idiot, half moron.
description: Johnny Tightlips, born Giovanni Silencio, also known by his legal name, Jonathan Schmallippe, is a frequently appearing mobster and the second-in-command of his old boss Fat Tony, as well as his current boss, Fit-Fat Tony.

name: Shauna Chalmers
occupation: Manager at Smart TykesKrusty Burger employee (formerly)Mother Hubbard's Sandwich Cupboard employee (formerly)Marijuana DealerStudent of Springfield High School
phrases: Im ShaunaAll seeing? Yeah, whens that last time you saw your feet?
Either the duck suffers or the kid does, or none of yous getting nothing from Shauna. Im Shauna.
description: Shauna Chalmers is the former girlfriend of Squeaky-Voiced Teen, Bart, and Jimbo. She is the daughter of Superintendent Chalmers and the late Rosemary Chalmers.

name: Rachel Jordan
description: Rachel Jordan is a 27-year-old woman who is the lead singer of Kovenant, a Christian rock band.

name: Gerald Samson
description: Gerald Samson, better known as "Baby Gerald" or "The Monobrow" (or "Unibrow Baby") (born January 12), is Maggie's nemesis. He has a uni-brow (hence his nickname). He made his first appearance in "Sweet Seymour Skinner's Baadasssss Song" (The 100th episode).

name: Michael D'Amico
description: Michael Earl D'Amico is Fat Tony and Anna Maria's son, and a student at Springfield Elementary School. Sherri and Terri describe him as "That weird kid who never says anything."

name: Bernice Hibbert
phrases: Ooh, Marge.
description: Bernice Hibbert (née Dupree) is Dr. Hibbert's wife. She is somewhat a heavy drinker. This has been joked about on at least one occasion (in "Homer vs. the Eighteenth Amendment", she faints, along with other imbibers of renown, upon reading the news that Prohibition has been introduced in Springfield) and she also stated once that she was too drunk to remember marrying her husband. She is usually friends with Marge and is a member of the Springfield Book Club along with Helen Lovejoy, Cookie Kwan, Agnes Skinner, Luann Van Houten, and Lindsey Naegle.

name: Cookie Kwan
phrases: Stay off the west side!
description: Cookie Kwan is a go-getter in the imploding Springfield real-estate industry, the self-proclaimed "number one on the west side." She is of Asian (possibly Chinese) heritage and has a stereotypical Asian accent, implying she's likely an immigrant. She works at Red Blazer Realty and considers herself a very eligible bachelorette.

name: Roger Meyers Jr.
phrases: Hey, great, mail it to last week—. Ive got cartoons to make.
description: Roger Meyers, Jr. is the son of Roger Meyers, Sr. and the current Chairman of Itchy & Scratchy Studios, which produces The Itchy & Scratchy Show. He distributes the cartoon, which is frequently criticized by parents because of its indulgently violent and lurid nature. His family name has been spelled as both "Meyers" and "Myers" - sometimes in the same episode. In some episodes, Roger Meyers, Jr. speaks with a nasally high-pitched Brooklyn accent.

name: Seymour Skinner (real)
description: Seymour "W." Skinner is a Sergeant in the U.S. Army, the son of Sheldon and Agnes Skinner. He dreamed of becoming principal of Springfield Elementary School, which he frequently told to the men under his command. After being captured by the enemy in Vietnam, he spent five years in a POW camp, before being sold to a shoe-producing company in the Chinese region of Wuhan, finally being released when the United Nations shut the sweatshop down. He then returned to Springfield, where he tried to take his life back, only to discover that one of the men who had once served in his unit, Armin Tamzarian, had moved to Springfield and assumed the identity of Seymour Skinner, to the point of living in his old house with his mother and even working in his dream job as the principal of Springfield Elementary.

name: Üter Zörker
description: Üter Zörker is an obese exchange student from Germany.

name: George Washington
occupation: Former U.S. President and Former Surveyor

name: Kevin (Stealing First Base)
occupation: 4th Grade Student at Springfield Elementary School
description: Kevin is a blind boy who is a student of Springfield Elementary School. He is in Audrey McConnell's fourth grade class.

name: Jebediah Springfield
phrases: A noble spirit embiggens the smallest man!
description: Hans Sprungfeld, better known as Jebediah Obadiah Zachariah Jedediah Springfield, was the purported historical founder of the town of Springfield and a murderous pirate.

name: Matt Groening
occupation: Creator of Futurama & Life in Hell
phrases: Your creator is TVs most beloved animation visionary.
description: Matt Groening is the creator of the television show Futurama, as well as the comic strip Life in Hell. He is also known for creating such comics as "Damnation", "Johnny Reb" and "True Murder Stories." He is also creating the television show Disenchantment, which is currently on Netflix.

name: Bill Clinton
occupation: Former President of the United States
phrases: I am Clin-ton. As overlord, all will kneel trembling before me and obey my brutal command. End communication.
description: William Jefferson "Bill" Clinton (born William Jefferson Blythe III on August 19, 1946) was the forty-second President of the United States, serving from 1993 to 2001. He has made several appearances in the show, voiced by Dan Castellaneta in Sunday, Cruddy Sunday, Bart Gets an Elephant & Weekend at Burnsie's, Phil Hartman in "Treehouse of Horror VII", and Karl Wiedergott in episodes since Season 10.

name: Dewey Largo
occupation: Music Teacher,Worker at Starving Teachers Moving Co.
phrases: Nobody likes Milhouse!
Simpson, do you find something funny about the word ¨TromBONER¨?!
description: Deward "Dewey" Largo, MMus, is the music teacher whom Lisa credited with proving that any piece of music could have the soul sucked out of it. He is very counter-creative and is a poor conductor. He is also 53 years old, and seems depressed/hot tempered.

name: Allison Taylor
description: Allison Taylor is a student at Springfield Elementary who is one of Lisa Simpson’s classmates. Allison is just as smart as Lisa, if not even smarter, and is also a year younger (having skipped a grade). Also like Lisa, she too is a talented saxophone player.

name: Darcy
phrases: I need strawberries right now.
Dad, lay off the Bartman.
description: Darcy is a 15-year-old girl that Bart Simpson once had a crush on from North Haverbrook.

description: The Grumple (also known as Grumpy Groo) is a green, hairy character (a parody of Dr. Seuss' the Grinch), which appears in Kill Gil: Vols. 1 & 2. He played a character that threatened to steal all of the Holiday cheer of the Winter Holidays in the Krusty’s Kristmas On Ice show. When a fight broke out between the basketball team and the show skaters (because the preparations for the upcoming game were ruining the show) Homer took matters to his own hands and fought the Grumple, demanding that he return the Holiday cheer. On Christmas Day, when Gil had all of his stuff stacked in the living room of the Simpsons House, Homer commented that this was a problem. Marge then commented that Homer had a bigger problem outside and pointed at the window. The Grumple was standing outside the house, holding a knife and proclaiming "Grumpily Grumpily Groo! Your blood will make my stew!" Homer suspects it was the same Grumple from the Ice Show. Sometime later in the year, while Gil was still mooching off the Simpsons, Homer was at Moe's Tavern and the Grumple attempted to attack again with a broken pool stick. Homer hit him with a beer bottle, knocking him unconscious, suddenly, some sort of green liquid began oozing out of the Grumple's eye, suggesting that it was not a human in a costume, but some sort of strange creature. The Grumple does not return until the following Christmas when the Simpson Family spend it at their condo in Scottsdale, Arizona with Gil, having brought his wife, son and daughter with him. The Grumple proclaims "Grumpily-grumpily-groo, we're here to share Christmas with you!" having put his feud with Homer aside as the humans and Grumples began singing Christmas Carols.

occupation: Former First Lady of the United States (1989-1993)
description: Barbara Pierce Bush was the wife of former President George H. W. Bush. She was seen living in the White House, and later moved into the house across the road from the Simpsons with her husband. She reflected some of her views during her husband's presidency, particularly when Bush Sr. was known for making the remark that "America needs to be a lot more like the Waltons and a lot less like the Simpsons". Barbara Bush had taken a softer stance to The Simpsons, saying that she would have enjoyed inviting Marge Simpson to a dinner at the White House if it was physically possible. She is shocked that when the Simpsons are touring the White House they feel entitled to go into the private quarters of the presidential family and that they see her in the bathtub. Despite being rightfully annoyed at first, Mrs. Bush softens her tone when she sees the Simpsons are wearing VIP badges. Later, Barbara Bush is much more courteous, making friends with Marge and she gets along quite well with Bart Simpson, despite the fact that Bart is a nuisance to her husband. Both Marge and Barbara are annoyed by the fact their husbands bicker and eventually fight, agreeing that both men act in a pig-headed manner.

name: Jay Sherman
phrases: It stinks!
description: Jay Sherman (full name Jay Prescott Sherman IV) is a movie critic who was the main character of The Critic. In "A Star is Burns", he came to Springfield to be a judge during the film festival. In "Hurricane Neddy", he was a patient at the Calmwood Mental Hospital. He also apparently became a regular patron to Moe's Tavern. Voiced by Jon Lovitz, Sherman was originally the main character on The Critic, which was created by Simpsons writers Al Jean and Mike Reiss. His character has been described as "balder than Siskel and fatter than Ebert". His appearance in "A Star is Burns" was a crossover to promote the second season of The Critic, which made its FOX debut on the same day after the episode premiered. The Critic was later canceled. Jay Sherman can burp very loudly. He mentioned that only one other person can belch as loudly as he can.

name: Princess Opal (Character)
description: Princess Opal is a fortune teller and owner of Princess Opal.

name: Evelyn
description: Evelyn is Patty's girlfriend.

name: Donald Trump
occupation: 45th President of the United States of America.
description: Donald John Trump Sr. (born June 14, 1946) is the 45th elected president of the United States. Prior to his election, Trump had been a prominent businessman, TV host of The Apprentice, and real estate developer. He also opened the Trump Taj Mahal in Atlantic City on Monday April 2, 1990.

name: Gary Coleman (character)
occupation: Security guard at Kid First Industries
description: Gary Coleman was the security guard at Kid First Industries and was on guard duty when Bart and Lisa snuck into Jim Hope's office seeking answers about Funzo. He later tried to stop Bart, Lisa and Homer from destroying all of the Funzos in the Springfield Tire Yard fire, but relented after he saw how evil they were. The Simpsons invited him to their home for Christmas dinner. However, at first, he refused, as he had other plans. He came anyway due to Lisa forcing him.

name: Rex (Bart of Darkness)
description: Rex is a student who attends Springfield Elementary.

name: Lisa's Classmate 6's Sister
description: Lisa's Classmate 6's Sister is the daughter of Female Unnamed with blonde and green dress and Officer Krackney.

name: Joseph Stalin
description: Joseph Stalin, known simply as Stalin was a former dictator of the Soviet Union.

name: Female Korean Artist 2 (couch gag)
description: Female Korean Artist 2 is a cartoonist seen coloring the Simpson family.

name: Mrs. Frink
description: Mrs. Frink is the wife of Professor Frink.

name: Martha Stewart (character)
description: Martha Stewart is an author and TV presenter.

name: Ham
description: Ham is a member and the leader of the Superfriends club, along with Database, Cosine, E-mail, Report Card and Lisa. He is a short, fat kid with suspenders, a bow-tie and glasses. His nickname comes from his enjoyment of ham radio. He makes the fourth most appearances out of The Superfriends (the three who make the most are Lisa, Cosine and Database).

name: Audrey McConnell's Student 4
phrases: (Speaking to Bart) Its a Japanese card game based on a cartoon based on an ancient religion based on a candy bar.
description: Audrey McConnell's Student 4 is an unnamed student at Springfield Elementary School.

name: Dr. Crab
description: Dr. Crab is a fictional character, Radioactive Man's nemesis and the central antagonist of the Radioactive Man comics. An inveterate Communist, he spoofs Communist supervillains such as Red Ghost,and Aleksander Lukin. He may have also been inspired by Red Skull, although that was originally written as a Nazi supervillain.

name: Marge Ziff
description: Marge Ziff is an alternate version of Marge Simpson who married Artie Ziff in the Treehouse of Horror segment, Bart and Homer's Excellent Adventure.

name: Lois Griffin
phrases: Oh, for Petes sake
description: Lois Patrice Commondenominator Griffin (née Pewterschmidt) (born June 3, 1956 in 1999; 1980 in 2023) is one of the two deuteragonists (alongside Brian Griffin) of the adult animated television series Family Guy. She is Peter Griffin's wife, Meg, Chris, and Stewie Griffin's mother, and the owner of a talking white Labrador Retriver, Brian Griffin.

name: Freedom
description: Freedom is a falcon that was owned by Diggs.

name: Judith Underdunk
description: Dame Judith Underdunk is the wife of Robert Terwilliger, Sr. and the mother of Sideshow Bob and Cecil Terwilliger. According to Lisa, she is a retired Shakespearean actress. Her sons get their extremely curly hair from her. Though she looks like an elderly female version of Sideshow Bob, she and Cecil share a similar nose structure.

name: Chief Inspector
occupation: Nuclear inspector at the Springfield Nuclear Power PlantDesigner at Powell MotorsResearch scientist at Tipsy McStagger's Good-Time Drinking and Eating Emporium
description: The Chief Inspector is a man who works as a nuclear inspector at the Springfield Nuclear Power Plant.

name: Miss Goodthighs
description: Miss Goodthighs is an employee at Globex Corporation.

name: Popular Girl 3
phrases: (Speaking to Lisa) Lisa, you want to come skip rope?
description: Popular Girl 3 is an unnamed student at Springfield Elementary School.

name: Bluella
description: Bluella was a female blue whale who washed up on the shore of Springfield.

name: Albert
phrases: That’s right! I don’t need this scooter! All of you, follow me to the future!

What Albert taught us is that all people have pride and no group should ever be insulted. He knew what was important was how you lived your life every day. Till he was taken from us too soon, at the age of... TWENTY-THREE?!? PEOPLE, FOR GOD’S SAKE, JOIN A GYM!
description: Albert was the leader of an overweight group. He was an activist for fat people's rights. He died after standing up from his scooter because he was so fat and unhealthy, even though he was only 23 years old. He was so fat, his cremated ashes needed nine urns and a large sack to contain them. Albert was suspended to a mobility scooter. If he tried to stand up (which he did), he would die.

name: Millionaire Actor
description: Millionaire Actor is Homer's relative, who appears when Homer tries to show Lisa how successful the Simpsons are. Judging by his appearance, he is most likely one of Homer's cousins.

name: Charles Bronson
description: Charles Bronson  was an American actor.

name: Mr. T
description: Laurence Tureaud, better known as Mr. T is an American actor best known for playing the character B.A.Baracus in the 1980s TV show The A-Team and Clubber Lang in the 1982 movie Rocky III.

name: Freddy Krueger
description: Freddy Krueger is a fictional character of the real world A Nightmare on Elm Street franchise.

name: Jeremy Jailbird
description: Jeremy Timothy Turley, or Jeremy Jailbird is a student and a friend of Bart and the son of Snake Jailbird and looks just like him. Snake suggests he go play with Bart. Jeremy asks Bart in a soft-spoken voice, "Do you like Xbox?" His parents are not together, but Snake apparently has visitation rights. He and Snake can briefly be seen boarding the ship to Weasel Island in "Moe Letter Blues".

name: The Thing
description: The Thing is a superhero who was seen fighting against The Incredible Hulk on behalf of the Protestant Unionists due to the fact he is orange. He was most probably sentenced later for the violence.

name: Teller
description: Teller is an American comedian, illusionist and writer. He is best known for his double-act with his fellow Penn Jillette.

name: Carol Berrera
occupation: Army Sergeant (retired)Fourth Grade Teacher at Springfield Elementary (formerly)

name: Jim-Jam Bonks
description: Jim-Jam Bonks is a fictional character in Cosmic Wars: The Gathering Shadow.

name: Dylan Spuckler
description: Dylan Spuckler is one of Cletus Spuckler and Brandine Spuckler's children.

name: The Raccoon Family
description: The Raccoon Family is a family of four raccoons that live in the Simpson's garden.

name: Benevenstanciano
description: Benevenstanciano was a friend of Marge Simpson's. He got her the most recent issues of the Sponge and Vacuum magazine, but Marge put it down and instead went with a more extreme magazine.

name: Cregg Demon
description: Cregg Demon is a man who is a magician and ran for Parliament in Canada.

name: Morty Szyslak
description: Mortimer "Morty"  Szyslak is the father of Szyslak children.

name: Armando (Barber)
description: Armando is Marge's hairdresser who works in The Perm Bank (also called Le Pamperie Hair Salon).

name: Richie Sakai
description: Richie Sakai is an anesthesiologist who sang in the karaoke bar at The Happy Sumo restaurant. He is modeled and named after long-time producer Richard Sakai. He sings "Gypsies, Tramps, and Thieves" which he dedicates to his wife, Pattie.

name: Frankie (Health Inspector)
phrases: Food hygienically stored... only one way to find out.
description: Frankie was a health inspector who entered Moe's Tavern one day for a routine inspection of the place.

name: Bud Armstrong
description: Bud Armstrong is the commissioner of Pro Football. He is a man who appears to be in his 50s with gray hair a black suit and nerdy glasses.

name: Vampiredna
phrases: Do not strugle, mortal! You cannot resist Vampiredna
description: Vampiredna was Edna Krabappel's superhero alter-ego when she was affected by a Nuclear Explosion.

name: Dr. Zweig
description: Dr. Zweig is a psychologist who helps Marge overcome her fear of flying.

name: Bender Bending Rodríguez
phrases: Bite my shiny metal ass!A robot! With a catchphrase!Kill all humans.Start with Flanders.
description: Bender Bending Rodríguez (born 2996), or better known as just Bender, is a robot of Matt Groening's other series, Futurama, in which he is voiced by John DiMaggio and plays the role of a comic anti-hero, and is described as an "alcoholic, whore-mongering, chain-smoking gambler". Bender canonically meets the Simpsons in the episode "Simpsorama".

name: Tyler's Brother
description: Tyler's Brother is a boy, who is a student at Springfield Elementary School.

name: Irving Zitsofsky
occupation: Tattoo Removal Specialist at Dr. Zitsofsky's Dermatology ClinicOwner of Dr. Zitsofsky's Dermatology Clinic

name: Minnie Szyslak
description: Minnie Szyslak is the sister of Moe Szyslak and is a mattress saleswoman and food critic.

name: Wizard Twins
description: The Wizard Twins are characters in the Angelica Button fantasy book series by T. R. Francis that are linked together, making it look like they have two heads.

name: Belle
description: Belle is an entrepreneuse and the proprietoress of a burlesque house in Springfield called "La Maison Derrière".

name: Dr. Octopus
description: Dr. Octopus is a supervillain who fights Spider-Man.

name: Christopher Columbus
description: Christopher Columbus was an Italian explorer, navigator and colonizer who discovered America.

name: Two-nicorn
description: The Two-nicorn is a unicorn in Equalia that not only has two horns, but can also burp out a rainbow.

name: Lisa's Classmate 5
description: Lisa's Classmate 5 is a boy in Ms. Hoover's second grade class. He is a very common character to see in the background of Lisa's class.

name: Daphne Burns
phrases: Mr. Burns has a mother? She must be a hundred million years old!
description: Daphne Burns (née Charles) was the only child of Jean-Claude Charles and Ophelia Charles and Charles Montgomery Burns' mother. She was married to Clifford Burns, and once had an affair with President Taft. She was born around the late 1850s to the early 1860s. Her date of death is unclear, with her appearing to either have died in the 1930s while Mr. Burns was still at school, or lived to 122 by the 1990s.

name: Jimbo Jr.
phrases: This cream corn tastes like cream crap!
description: James “Jimbo” Jones, Jr., is Jimbo's son in the future, at least what Bart thinks when in the future he thinks he will be a lunch lady serving Jimbo Junior. Jimbo Junior says, "This cream corn tastes like cream crap." This fantasy is sparked by Bart fearing Principal Skinner's potential punishment after finding out Bart cut class.

name: Jack Larson
description: Jack Larson was a slick spokesman and now president for Laramie Cigarettes. He was seen calming the crowd after a truckload of Laramie Cigarettes were stolen by Fat Tony and the Springfield Mafia (much to his distaste). He also was the spokesperson in a commercial for the Little Miss Springfield pageant, with Laramie cigarettes as the main sponsor. This advertisement was seen by Homer while watching TV at Moe’s.

name: Zachary Vaughn
occupation: Former teacher at Springfield Elementary School
phrases: hair............HAIR!!!!!!!!!!!Every class is a joke. English a joke, homeroom a joke. Free period a joke. Nutritious lunch a joke! Only alcohol can make life bearable. You must drink! Always drink!
description: Zachary Vaughn is the teacher that replaced Edna Krabappel as the fourth-grade teacher at Springfield Elementary School.

name: Guitarist
occupation: Guitarist for The Larry Davis Experience
description: The Guitarist is a guitarist for the The Larry Davis Experience. He first appeared in Some Enchanted Evening, where he and the rest of the band are playing at the Ye Olde Off-Ramp Inn.

name: Bart Junior (frog)
description: Bart Junior was a frog that Bart caught. It was later brought over to Australia but was released into the wild since Bart was not allowed to bring in foreign animals. Bart placed it in a fountain outside of the customs planning to pick it up on the way home. However, it jumped out of a window and was taken away by a kangaroo. The next day the entire of Australia was infested with Bullfrogs, all which were the offspring of Bart Junior.

name: Guy Incognito
phrases: Greetings, good man. Might I trouble you for a drink?
Homer? Who is Homer?
description: Guy Incognito is a man who is Homer's doppelganger, with the exception of a brown mustache. It is evident he has never met or heard of Homer Simpson, but his uncanny resemblance had gotten him into trouble.

name: Retirement Castle Nurse
description: The Retirement Castle Nurse is a nurse who works at the Springfield Retirement Castle, and sometimes other hospitals. She gives medicine to the old residents, not letting the old folks do anything and other boring things. She has an angry personality and is bored when she works. In earlier seasons (notably Raging Abe), she seemed dedicated to protecting the castle resident, literally firing a shotgun at the Hitman in "Raging Abe Simpson and His Grumbling Grandson in "The Curse of the Flying Hellfish".

name: Grandma Van Houten
description: "Grandma" Van Houten is Milhouse Van Houten's paternal grandmother and Kirk Van Houten's mother.

name: Hugs Bunny
occupation: Referee at Mayor's Easter Egg Hunt
description: Hugs Bunny is a referee at the Mayor's Easter Egg Hunt. Despite his name, however, Hugs Bunny, or at least his cosplayer, refuses to actually hug the children, claiming he's legally forbidden to do, probably because he was forbidden to hug children by Quimby's wife.

name: Justin's father
description: Justin's father is man whose son Justin likes William Shakespeare.

name: Abraham Simpson I
description: Abraham Simpson I was the paternal great-grandfather and namesake of Grampa Simpson, and thus the paternal great-great-grandfather of Homer Simpson and the paternal great-great-great-grandfather of Bart, Lisa, and Maggie. He was also the son of Virgil and Mabel Simpson, and the maternal half-brother of Eliza Simpson.

name: Joshua and Amber's Mom
description: Joshua and Amber's Mom is a woman who has two children, Joshua and Amber, although she only chooses one child to love. Joshua is great at football and Amber got the lead in the school play. She normally uses their grades as a tie-breaker, but one year they both got straight A's. She presumably has a husband who works at the Springfield Nuclear Power Plant, as she attends Mr. Burns's family picnic, where she gets drunk on punch and befriends Marge Simpson. She later sings a song with Marge.

name: James L. Brooks (character)
description: James L. Brooks is a famous writer for TV shows. He first appears as a still in the The Simpsons 138th Episode Spectacular, although here he is portrayed as fat, wealthy tycoon with many entertainment awards.

name: Mayor Quimby's Bodyguards
description: Mayor Quimby's Bodyguards are a duo of Bodyguards that Mayor Quimby has to guard him. However, they are sometimes lazy and slack off, looking at the sky when the mayor is in danger. This results in them getting fired and being replaced by Homer although they eventually return. They are implied to be romantically involved with each other.

name: Lisa's Classmate 2
description: Lisa's Classmate 2 is an unnamed character in Ms. Hoover's second grade class.

name: Sherri and Terri's sister
description: Sherri and Terri's sister is the sister of the twins Sherri and Terri. She was mentioned by J. Loren Pyror during his meeting with Bart; during this, he stated that Sherri, Terri, and the unnamed sister were conjoined triplets, and the third triplet is out seeking revenge after being separated from her sisters.

name: Della
occupation: Lionel Hutz's secretaryEmployee at Shotgun Pete's (formerly)
phrases: Calls?...Oh, Calls. The Supreme Court called again. They need your help in some freedom thing.
description: Della is Lionel Hutz's secretary who does not appear to be a very good secretary, and has also worked at Shotgun Pete's 24 Hour Wedding Chapel.

name: Drederick Tatum
description: Drederick Earl Tatum is a former boxer who resides in Springfield. Heavily based on Mike Tyson, Tatum is known for his extremely large size, his success at boxing (former Olympian and World Heavyweight Champion), his ever-present lisp, and a long and troubled history of violent outbursts and incidents. He seems to have retired from boxing in recent years.

name: Giuseppe
description: Giuseppe is the monkey often seen with Luigi Risotto.

name: McBain
phrases: Ice to see you!
description: McBain is a fictional action movie hero played by the actor Rainier Wolfcastle in the McBain movies. His name is a play on the character John McClane of the Die Hard series, and his appearance and personality are inspired by Bruce Willis (sarcasm), Arnold Schwarzenegger (towering height, extremely strong, limited emotional range and thick Austrian accent) and Clint Eastwood (carries a large caliber revolver as a duty sidearm). McBain movies feature numerous action movie clichés, such as a policeman being gunned down just before retirement, guns that never run out of ammunition, considerable (and often unnecessary) property damage, and cheesy one-liners.

name: Postage Stamp Fellow
description: Mr. Albertson (also known as Postage Stamp Fellow) is the father of Comic Book Guy.

name: Nabendu Nahasapeemapetilon
phrases: Back.
description: Nabendu Nahasapeemapetilon is one of The Nahasapeemapetilon Octuplets. He is the son of Apu and Manjula.

name: Vincent Price
description: Vincent Price was an American actor.

name: Tiffany Spuckler
description: Tiffany Spuckler is one of Cletus Spuckler and Brandine Spuckler's children.

name: Scary Vultures
description: The Scary Vultures are vultures that hang around Springfield National Forest, where they prey on the Simpsons. They can later be seen following Maggie. A pair of vultures can also be seen in attacking Homer and Ned, but it is unlikely they are the same ones.

name: William Shakespeare
description: William Shakespeare was an English poet and playwright, widely regarded as the greatest writer in the English language.

name: Cap'n Crunch
description: Cap'n Crunch is a mascot for the Cap'n Crunch's cereals.

name: John Travolta
description: John Travolta appears in the 70's bar at the theme park Itchy & Scratchy Land. Marge says that the bartender even looks like John Travolta. John replies "Yeah, Looks like." He also appears in "Beyond Blunderdome" as Mel Gibson's pilot, on the condition that he assists John in moving.

name: Jay Leno
description: Jay Leno is an American comedian and television host. He's also famous for being a car collector, with over 286 vehicles.

name: Tribal Chief
description: The Tribal Chief is the manager of Caesar's Pow-Wow Casino.

name: Seth
occupation: Owner of Groovy Grove Juice Corporation
description: Seth is one of Homer's hippie friends. He is a co-owner of the Groovy Grove Juice Corporation (along with Munchie), and was a friend of Mona Simpson in the 1960s. He is heavily implied to have enjoyed a sexual relationship with her.

name: Kermit the Frog
description: Kermit is a frog from the Muppets. Jim Henson's most famous Muppet creation. Kermit was first introduced in 1955. He is the main character in many Muppet/Henson projects, most notably as host and star of The Muppet Show, very well known for various roles on Sesame Street, in commercials and in public service announcements over the years. He was in a film with Troy McClure called "The Muppets Go Medival". He was also seen in a TV program when Lurleen Lumpkin was singing "Bunk with Me Tonight" to him. He was then beaten up by Miss Piggy.

name: Justin Timberlake
description: Justin Timberlake is an American singer.

name: Mrs. Dexter
description: Mrs. Dexter is a kind woman who lives in a house on Evergreen Terrace. She has two children, one boy and one girl.

name: Robby the Automaton
description: Robby the Automaton is a robot used to promote the Springfield Knowledgeum. He is brought to Edna Krabappel's class telling the students about the Knowledgeum. He was believed to speak and move by himself, but Bart saw the man controlling the robot from outside the classroom. When Bart knocked out the man by throwing an apple at him, the robot reverted to default setting ("Crush! Kill! Destroy!") and started strangling Skinner, much to the students' amusement.

name: Ms. Finch
occupation: Employee at the Springfield Nuclear Power Plant
description: Ms. Finch is an employee at the Springfield Nuclear Power Plant.

name: Hurt Leg Simpson Relative
phrases: My legs hurt.
description: "Hurt Leg" is Homer's relative, who appears when Homer tries to show Lisa how successful the Simpsons are. When Homer asks him what he does for a living his only reply is "my leg hurts." He wears a gray hoodie and sweatpants.

name: Mrs. Szyslak
description: Mrs. Szyslak was the real mother of Moe Szyslak, Stringfellow Szyslak, Gandamac Szyslak, Marv Szyslak and Minnie Szyslak. She was also the wife of Morty Szyslak.

name: Benjamin
description: Benjamin is one of three nerds that Homer met at Springfield University. He is thin with red hair and a big nose.

name: Birch Barlow
description: Birchibald "Birch" T. Barlow is a right-wing conservative talk show host on the radio station KBBL. He also has a show on Fox News.

name: Milo
phrases: Now I hope you all like Korean Pop Covers of Tom Jones songs, cause theyre about to be blasted!
description: Milo is the owner of Coolsville Comics & Toys. He is the complete opposite of Comic Book Guy.

name: Snowball II
description: Snowball II was the Simpson family's second cat. Snowball II was named after Snowball I. Though Snowball I had white fur, which obviously inspired her name, Snowball II had black fur and greenish/yellow eyes.

name: Mary Spuckler
description: Mary WrestleMania Spuckler is one of Cletus's many children. She is forced to marry Bart in order to save Lou. Bart and Mary end up not getting married but develop a genuine attraction which leads to an on-and-off romance. Their relationship has been explored in three episodes, making her the most prominent of Bart's love interests and Bart's first serious relationship.

name: Woman Interviewer
description: The Woman Interviewer is a woman who interviewed the "Bride of Bigfoot".

name: Singapore
description: Singapore is a country of Asia.

name: Burglar 2 (couch gag)
description: Burglar 2 is a thief seen, along with Burglar 1, stealing the Simpson's couch.

name: Tito Puente (character)
description: Tito Puente is a Latin-American jazz musician and bandleader who was a music teacher at Springfield Elementary School for a brief time. He was also a suspect in the attempted murder of Charles Montgomery Burns.

name: Richard's Grandmother
description: Richard's Grandmother have a blue bike.

name: Adrian Belew
phrases: Over here, Mr. President.
description: Adrian Belew is a boy in Bart Simpson's class. He shares his name with a real-life session guitarist known for his work on Paul Simon's album Graceland.

name: Wile E. Coyote
description: Wile E. Coyote is an adult male coyote who appeared on a Couch gag, in which he paints a fake couch on the living room wall which The Simpsons run into and get hurt.

name: Great Mom
description: The Great Mom is a woman who is the wife of Great Dad and the mother of her son and daughter. She attends Mr. Burns' company picnic with the rest of her family, where she pities Homer's sad life. However, they are later unhappy and are looking for therapy at Dr. Monroe's Family Therapy Center. They flee when the Simpson family draw power while getting electric shock therapy from the building and, later, the whole area of Springfield.

name: Fallout Boy
phrases: Jiminy jillickers!
description: Fallout Boy is the sidekick in the comic book series Radioactive Man. He was introduced in issue #9 of the comic, and also appeared in a TV series shown at a comic book convention, played by Buddy Hodges.

name: Rupert Murdoch (character)
description: Rupert Murdoch is the owner of FOX and many other companies.

name: Angry Mob
phrases: Ah, theres no justice like angry mob justice.
description: Springfield's Angry Mob is a recurring group throughout the Simpsons series, consisting of many of the townspeople of Springfield and usual secondary characters (including Abe Simpson and excluding the Flanders family, with occasional exceptions). They would angrily, and violently react to generally minor situations, and would often go after the Simpson family or at least another certain character on any given occasion.

name: Russ Cargill
description: Russell ''Russ'' Cargill is the main antagonist of The Simpsons Movie. He was the leader of the EPA and the Head of the Dome operation in The Simpsons Movie. At first, he seemed to have been acting out for the safety for the environment, but he gradually goes mad with power, and plans to blow up all of Springfield with a powerful time bomb.

name: Gort
description: Gort is a fictional robot from the 1951 movie "The Day the Earth Stood Still", he spent his time defending his partner, Klatuu.

name: Ishmael
description: Ishmael was a student at the Springfield Elementary School. He and his brother Ezekiel were in the same class with Bart. They are now presumably taught at Springfield Christian School.

name: Raphael
phrases: Mmm-hmm...Ey, pal-ey.
description: Raphael (also commonly known as the Sarcastic Clerk, Wiseguy, or Middle-Aged Man) is a recurring background character in The Simpsons - his main purpose is to carry out a job or sell a product that gets a plot rolling. His voice is also often used for loudspeaker announcements.

name: George H. W. Bush
occupation: Former Vice President and President of the United States  Member of the Stonecutters World Council
description: George Herbert Walker Bush (June 12, 1924-November 30, 2018) was the former Vice President and President of the United States and neighbor of the Simpson family on Evergreen Terrace. He's also a member of the World Council of the Sacred Order of the Stonecutters.

name: Lilly Ellison
description: Lilly Ellison is a girl who attends Springfield Elementary School.

name: Les Moore
phrases: NaturallyCan I offer you a drink to throw at my face?There you are, old pal.

name: Willie's Mother
description: Willie's Mother, also known as Mrs. MacDougal, is the unnamed mother of Groundskeeper Willie. She lives in Scotland and owns a small bar there.

name: Player 1
occupation: Video-game character used by the first player in Super Slugfest
description: Player 1 is a character that the first player uses in the video game Super Slugfest, who appears in Moaning Lisa. He is played by Homer. It is later played by Martin in the music video for Deep, Deep Trouble.

name: Bashir bin Laden
description: Bashir bin Laden is a Jordanian Muslim boy who moved to America with his family. He attends Springfield Elementary School. He is good friends with Bart Simpson.

name: FBI agent (Donnie Fatso)
description: FBI agent was an agent who worked with Homer Simpson.

name: Iggy Wiggum
description: Ignatius "Iggy" Wiggum is the deceased father of Clancy Wiggum, Springfield's Chief of Police, father-in-law of Sarah Wiggum and paternal grandfather of Ralph Wiggum. He was one of the members of the Flying Hellfish in World War II.

name: Male Korean Artist 3 (couch gag)
description: Male Korean Artist 3 is a cartoonist seen coloring the Simpson family.

name: Mike (Homer's Night Out)
description: Mike is a man who is the father of Freddy.

name: Nibbles
description: Nibbles was the class hamster of Springfield Elementary.

name: Ian (Very Tall Man)
occupation: Writer for The Itchy & Scratchy Show
phrases: Do you find something comical about my appearance when I am driving my automobile?
description: Ian is a man who goes around teaching bullies a lesson because he got bullied from second grade to high school.

name: Parasite
description: Parasite is a fictional mouse who appears in The Worker & Parasite Show alongside Worker. When Itchy and Scratchy left The Krusty the Clown Show, they got this cartoon instead. They were "Eastern Europe's favorite cat and mouse team."

name: David Copperfield
description: David Copperfield is a world famous American illusionist. He is also the most commercially successful magician in history.

name: Coach Krupt
phrases: Today were going to play a game as old as pain itself, bombardment.DUCK OR DIE!BOMBARDMENT!
description: Coach Krupt is the sadist gym teacher at Springfield Elementary School.

name: Ramrod
description: Ramrod is a biker and a member of the Hell's Satans.

name: Mr. Rhenquist
description: Mr. Frank Rhenquist is Francine Rhenquist's father.

name: Darryl
description: Darryl is a student at Springfield Elementary School.

name: Freddy
description: Freddy is a boy who is a student at Springfield Elementary School and is friends with Milhouse Van Houten.

name: Leopold
description: Leopold is Superintendent Chalmers' assistant. He is a large, surly, snarling man. When Principal Skinner had to be replaced, Leopold stomped in, issued several threats, horrified children by making them think he was the replacement, and then suddenly politely introduced the actual substitute, Ned Flanders. The children then collectively sighed with relief. The gag was repeated when Marge Simpson became a substitute teacher when the teachers go on strike.

name: Snowball III
description: Snowball III was the third cat owned by the Simpsons.

name: Gill-man
description: The Gill-man is a monster from the 1954 movie Creature from the Black Lagoon.

name: Joe Frazier
description: Joe Frazier was a professional boxer.

name: John (Homer's Phobia)
phrases: No, ultrasuede is a miracle. This is just good timing.
Zap

phrases: Hey Bart. Remember, if you see a gold brick lying around just take it! Take it! Take it! Take it!... Take it!
description: Sonic the Hedgehog is the protagonist of the eponymous video game series, and has served as Sega's company mascot since the release of his first game in 1991. Sonic's sidekick and best friend is named Miles "Tails" Prower, who is a two tailed fox. His first rival is Knuckles the Echidna. He has a troublesome self-proclaimed girlfriend named Amy Rose, who is trying to have a date with him despite his lack of interest. His nemesis is called Dr. Ivo Robotnik, who now goes by the name Dr. Eggman (or simply Eggman) which was once a nickname given to him by the Blue Blur himself, until he adopted it. Sonic is known usually for his speed and his attitude. He believes that life should be fun.

name: Mr. Blackheart

Suspicious of his true intentions, Lisa asks if he's an ivory dealer, only to admit that not only he's one, but that he had previously hunted whales and clubbed seals in his previous jobs. Hearing this, Bart tries to reasonate with Homer to not sell Stampy to him, but after failing and taking the offer, he ran away alongside Stampy. The following morning after the Simpsons notice their dissapearance, Homer curses his name, mistakingly thinking that he took Bart alongside Stampy.

description: Captain Lance Murdock is a professional stunt devil who broke every single bone in his body while doing his stunts. One stunt had him jumping a pool filled with Great White Sharks, Electric Eels, a school of Piranhas, alligators, and one lion, as well as the water itself containing an element of human blood. Although he got through the stunt itself in one piece, he ended up clumsily falling in while basking in the glory afterward, swimming to the edge only to be pulled back in by a lion, and had to be netted out by paramedics and put on a stretcher, barely surviving. He inspired Bart Simpson to become a daredevil and convinced him personally to jump over Springfield Gorge on a skateboard. After Homer ended up hospitalized after he had inadvertently jumped the gorge in Bart's place in an attempt to stop him (as well as falling down the gorge again due to the ambulance driving into a tree), he ended up being the neighboring patient of Lance Murdock, with Homer bitterly telling him "You think you've got guts? name: John F. Kennedy
occupation: Former President of the United States
description:
John Fitzgerald Kennedy (May 29, 1917 - November 22, 1963) was the president of the United States from 1961 until his assassination in 1963. He appeared in an advert for Duff Beer along with Richard Nixon. 
During the Season 6 episode Marge in Chains, Marge is accused of being an accomplice in Kennedy's asassination during trial proceedings surrounding  accusations of shoplifting the Kwiki-Mart. Professor Frink suggests her likeness was spotted "on the grassy knoll" 137 - 200 frames prior to Kennedy's fatal asassination in the Zapruder film. 
Homer watched him on TV when he was a boy.
Grampa found out he was sympathetic to the Nazis and had him beaten up when he overheard him say, "Ich bin ein Berliner."
He also appeared in Lisa's dream, where Lisa said that she would see him in Heaven, though he then went to Hell laughing after awkwardly acknowledging Heaven in response. He also may have been the president alluded to by Steve in Secret Nuclear Defense Plan U.S. Govt. Film #1612 due to the monochrome display suggesting a time frame between the late 1940s and early 1960s, although the lack of a mention to a specific time frame for the film does not make this clear. After falling into a nuclear bunker in Gone Boy, Bart watched  the real, non-animated Kennedy First Inauguration Speech and mocked it by sarcastically saying "Doesn't sound like any President I know." He is voiced in exactly the same way as Joe Quimby.

description: Linguo was a grammar-correcting robot created by Lisa for the science fair. Whenever Linguo detects a grammatical error it responds with the correct answer. Homer nearly destroys Linguo when he mistakes it for a toy robot and gives it beer. Lisa fixes Linguo, but it is later destroyed when members of the Springfield Mafia make numerous grammatical errors in its presence, causing an overload of Linguo's circuits. Linguo's last words are voiced in correction of Homer: "Linguo is dead."

description: Stewart Gilligan "Stewie" Griffin is the youngest member of the Griffin family in Family Guy. He is the intelligent, flamboyant and eccentric 1-year-old baby of Peter and Lois Griffin. Stewie, equipped with his teddy bear, Rupert, and his laser gun, has, on several occasions, almost single-handedly taken over the world and he seems to be obsessed with world domination and matricide. Despite being baptized by his step grandfather, Francis Griffin, he still remains completely evil nonetheless. He speaks with a British accent and he is best friends with his family's dog Brian Griffin.

name: Smilin' Joe Fission
description: Smilin' Joe Fission is the official mascot of the Springfield Nuclear Power Plant and the Springfield Isotopes. He also stars in filmstrips shown to visitors at the Power Plant, like the filmstrip the plant shows Bart's class. He looks similar to The Happy Little Elves. In the episode "Fatzcarraldo" Mr. Burns is seen disposing his body.

name: Fernando Vidal
description: Fernando Vidal was a professional killer, known as "the world's most devious assassin." After the death of Asa Phelps left Abe Simpson and Charles Montgomery Burns the sole surviving members of the Flying Hellfish, Burns hired Fernando Vidal to hasten Abe's demise. Vidal first attempted to poison Abe's dentures, but that failed, and later, he disguised himself as Homer Simpson (badly), with Burns dressed as Marge and Smithers dressed as Bart, and tried to throw a knife at Abe. His final attempt, which he claimed to be his most ingenious, involved simply bursting into the retirement home armed with a machine gun and shooting the place up, however he was driven away when one of the nurses pulled out a shotgun and fired at him for disturbing the residents. He is also apparently a part-time drug dealer as he mistakes Mr. Burns' initials for former D.C. Mayor Marion Barry, who was arrested by the FBI on drug charges.

description: Adil Hoxha was a foreign exchange student from Albania. He stayed with the Simpson family while Bart was in France, and was discovered to be a Communist spy. He is a main character in the Season One episode The Crepes of Wrath, where he makes his first (and to date only) significant appearance in the series.

description: Arnold William "Arnie" Pye is a disgruntled, somewhat eccentric helicopter traffic reporter for Springfield’s KBBL-TV (Channel 6). His segments are titled Arnie Pye with Arnie in the Sky. His accent implies that he may have originated from New York or New Jersey. His name is a play on "Ernie Pyle", a famous news reporter. He was called Bill Pye in "Some Enchanted Evening", and his name is spelled Arnie Pie in some of the Simpsons Comics issues. A running gag is when he is envious of Kent Brockman's TV fame, and argues with him on the air. Arnie Pye is 37 years old.
